      "description": "This 2001 BMW M3 (E46) is a museum-grade example of the legendary S54-powered coupe. The 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six features individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a razor-sharp throttle response and a mechanical 8,000 RPM redline. Power is routed through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to the factory variable M-differential. This specimen is mechanically impeccable, featuring a reinforced rear subframe, updated rod bearings, and a recently calibrated VANOS system. The chassis maintains its original rigidity, and the suspension retains its factory-spec damping characteristics. Finished in Carbon Black over Nappa leather, the paint depth and interior trim are flawless, showing no signs of UV degradation or bolster wear. A turn-key investment for the purist collector.",
